{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b1f5e9a0-7c3d-4e8a-9f21-tms0000000001",
    "name": "Translation Management Service API",
    "description": "REST API for storing, searching and exporting localized translations.\n\n## Getting started\n1. Set the `base_url` collection variable if your server is not on http://localhost:8005.\n2. Run **Authentication > Login** — the returned token is saved automatically to the `token` variable.\n3. Every other request inherits bearer auth from the collection, so they just work.\n4. Run **Translations > Create Translation** — the new id is saved to `translation_id`, so Show/Update/Delete work without editing anything.\n\nDefault credentials: admin@example.com / password\n\n## Response shape\nEvery JSON response uses one envelope:\n\n    { \"status\": \"success|failed\", \"code\": <http>, \"message\": \"...\", \"data\": <payload|null> }\n\n- List endpoints place the paginated payload at `data.data`, with `data.links` and `data.meta`.\n- Validation errors (422) place the field errors at `data`.\n- The only exception is **Export**, which returns a raw flat `{\"key\":\"value\"}` map (no envelope) for direct frontend i18n consumption.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8005", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "translation_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('status code is 200', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
                  "pm.test('envelope status is success', () => res.status === 'success');",
                  "pm.test('a token is returned', () => Boolean(res.data && res.data.token));",
                  "",
                  "if (res.data && res.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', res.data.token);",
                  "    console.log('Token saved to the `token` collection variable.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"admin@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"password\",\n    \"device_name\": \"postman\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate and receive a Sanctum bearer token.\n\nResponse: `{status, code, message, data: {user, token, token_type}}`. The test script stores `data.token` in the `token` variable automatically. Invalid credentials return `422` with errors under `data`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Current User",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Return the currently authenticated user.\n\nResponse: `{status, code, message, data: {id, name, email}}`. Returns `401` if the token is missing or revoked."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/logout",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "logout"]
            },
            "description": "Revoke the access token used for this request.\n\nResponse: `{status, code, message, data: null}` with HTTP `200`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Translations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List & Search",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/translations?per_page=50",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "translations"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "per_page", "value": "50" },
                { "key": "locale", "value": "en", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "key", "value": "homepage", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "content", "value": "welcome", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "tags[]", "value": "web", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "tags[]", "value": "mobile", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "cursor", "value": "", "disabled": true }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Cursor-paginated list. Enable any of the disabled query params to filter by locale, key prefix, content (full-text), or tags. Filters combine with AND.\n\nResponse: `{status, code, message, data: {data: [...translations], links, meta}}` — the items are at `data.data`, the pagination cursor at `data.meta.next_cursor`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Translation",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('status code is 201', () => pm.response.code === 201);",
                  "pm.test('envelope status is success', () => res.status === 'success');",
                  "",
                  "if (res.data && res.data.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('translation_id', res.data.id);",
                  "    console.log('translation_id set to ' + res.data.id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"locale\": \"en\",\n    \"key\": \"homepage.title\",\n    \"content\": \"Welcome\",\n    \"tags\": [\"web\", \"mobile\"]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/translations",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "translations"]
            },
            "description": "Create a translation. `tags` is optional; unknown tags are created automatically.\n\nResponse: `{status, code: 201, message, data: {id, key, content, locale, tags, ...}}`. The test script saves `data.id` to the `translation_id` variable. Validation errors return `422` with field errors under `data`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Show Translation",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/translations/{{translation_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "translations", "{{translation_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Fetch a single translation by id.\n\nResponse: `{status, code, message, data: {id, key, content, locale, tags, ...}}`. Returns `404` (`{status: failed, code: 404, ...}`) if the id does not exist."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Translation",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"content\": \"Welcome back\",\n    \"tags\": [\"web\"]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/translations/{{translation_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "translations", "{{translation_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Partial update — send only the fields you want to change (locale, key, content, tags).\n\nResponse: `{status, code, message, data: {...updated translation}}`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Translation",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/translations/{{translation_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "translations", "{{translation_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Delete a translation.\n\nResponse: `{status: success, code: 200, message: \"Translation deleted successfully.\", data: null}`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Export (flat JSON for frontends)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/translations/export?locale=en",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "translations", "export"],
              "query": [{ "key": "locale", "value": "en" }]
            },
            "description": "Export a locale's translations.\n\nUnlike every other endpoint, this returns a RAW flat map — `{\"homepage.title\": \"Welcome\", \"auth.login\": \"Log in\"}` — with no envelope, so it can be consumed directly by Vue.js / vue-i18n. Send the response `ETag` back as an `If-None-Match` header to receive `304 Not Modified` when nothing changed."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
